  "text": "Anaesthesia is most commonly maintained with opioids and inhalational anaesthetics in a mixture of oxygen and air or oxygen and nitrous oxide. Due to its irritating effects on the airway, desflurane should be avoided in children with asthma [CITATION_1] .",
